  "name": "Statins and MACE - Troponin Threshold Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find AMI confirmation via the PheKB-published troponin threshold: Troponin-I ≥0.10 ng/mL. This is the primary biomarker confirming AMI in the BioVU algorithm.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated cardiac troponin I above 0.10 ng/mL, suggesting myocardial injury.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high troponin.",
    "broad": "Find patients with elevated cardiac troponin I — at least 0.10 ng/mL — indicating myocardial injury and consistent with acute MI per the BioVU algorithm.",
    "expert": "I need to find patients with elevated cardiac troponin I consistent with acute myocardial infarction, using the threshold defined by the PheKB BioVU algorithm. Query Observation resources for cardiac troponin I in serum or plasma using the appropriate LOINC code, and filter for values at or above the AMI confirmation threshold — specifically a troponin I level of at least 0.10 ng/mL. This is the primary biomarker confirming AMI in the BioVU phenotype algorithm."
  },
